      <h1 class='title'>Hamer Report</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 04 May 2004 vol 420 c69WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_69ws' title='Col. 69WS &mdash; HC Deb 04 May 2004 vol 420 c69WS' name='column_69ws' href='#column_69ws' rel='bookmark'>69WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0420P2_20040504_CWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-hazel-blears' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0420P2_20040504_CWS_1' title='Link to this speech by Ms Hazel Blears' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-hazel-blears" title="Ms Hazel Blears">The Minister for Crime Reduction, Policing and Community Safety (Ms Hazel Blears)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">I have today placed in the Library of the House copies of the final report of the "Independent Review of the Selection and Appointments Process of Independent Members of Police Authorities", undertaken on behalf of the Home Secretary by Mr. Kenneth Hamer.</p><p>This report makes a range of recommendations to improve the selection and appointments process to key posts in police authorities, highlighting the need to engage local people and the importance of police authorities continuing to develop effective links with other community groups.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
